Their Royal Highnesses The Duke and Duchess of Cambridge landed in Cyprus for the day. 🇨🇾

They were at RAF Akrotiri to visit servicemen and women stationed at the base. The pair made the trip (about a 4-1/2 hour flight) aboard an RAF Voyager jet. They wanted to recognize and spend time with those far away from home during the holidays. 🎄

“You don’t seek praise for your contribution … But as we approach Christmas, Catherine and I feel strongly that praise for your work and recognition of your sacrifices is exactly what is due to you all. From my time in uniform, we both know a bit of what it feels like to balance your work commitments with your family life.
On behalf of everyone back home, we would like to say thank you. Thank you for your commitment and thank you for your sacrifices. We are in your debt and Catherine and I feel very lucky to be able to spend time with you today.” — The Prince of Wales 

The couple also officially opened a new OASIS welfare center, a dedicated space “where anyone serving on ops or living here permanently can come to relax.”

The paparazzi really are scum. Swipe for two videos of The Princess of Wales; turn up volume.

The first video is of Kate Middleton on her 25th birthday. The photographers regularly camped outside her private residence. She was just trying to go to work and had no security or protection of any kind.

The second video (audio only) is of Kate walking home at night with her sister Pippa. At least fifteen men chased her, harassed her, called her names, then laughed when she started crying.

This treatment went on for over a decade. I don’t know how she did stood it. I would not have lasted, even for true love. 

Could you do it?

President Biden said in a speech announcing the release of Brittney Griner that the U.S. was still seeking the release of Paul Whelan, a former Marine who has also been held by Russia.

Biden says Russia is treating the Paul Whelan case “differently - for totally illegitimate reasons.” He added that, “while we have not yet succeeded in securing Paul’s release we are not giving up. We will never give up. This was not a choice of which Americans to bring home.” 

The brother of Paul Whelan, said they were told beforehand he would not be included in the swap and were "able to mentally prepare for what is now a public disappointment for us."

David Whelan made sure to note he and his family were happy Griner has been released and said he knew the cases "were not intertwined."

"There is no greater success than for a wrongful detainee to be freed and for them to go home," he wrote. "The Biden Administration made the right decision to bring Ms. Griner home, and to make the deal that was possible, rather than waiting for one that wasn't going to happen."

Paul Whelan, the 52-year-old former Marine was given a 16-year jail sentence after being arrested in Moscow on suspicion of spying in 2018. 

From @mosheh. Great news page. Follow him if you don’t!
Throwing it back to their early days 💗

For all the armchair diplomats and international lawyers out there who are complaining about Brittney Griner’s release, especially the ones coming at me on my page and in my DMs, you may want to consider the following:

* The family of American prisoner Paul Whelan fully backs the Griner deal. 

* Russia refused to include or consider Paul Whelan in any exchange for Russian arms dealer Viktor Bout.  According to one high level US official: “It was a choice to get Brittney or nothing.”

I’ve found it’s very helpful to know facts before you announce your opinion. Maybe that’s just me. 

Thoughts and prayers for Paul and the Whelan family. Let’s hope he’s next. I fear he won’t survive another 12 years in such horrible conditions. 🙏🏼🙏🏼🙏🏼

From his website: 

Blaha Endurance Coaching: Personalized coaching for every runner 

A freshman NCAA Division I, Ivy League runner for Columbia University, George Blaha brings experience competing under coaches at the elementary, middle school, high school, and collegiate level, including famed coach Tom Schwartz, former Atlanta Track Club elite team member Patrick Peterson, legendary GA high school coaches Jolie and Steve Cunningham, and the current Columbia coaching staff. 

Blaha began his running career in fourth grade running local 5k races. He now competes against the best in the country (along with his twin brother Edward). He brings a wealth of knowledge about not just training, but also nutrition, recovery, and competitive mentality.

By @jmidy (swipe for more Ella pics 🙏🏼❤️🐾)

Whether you have had a dog or not, all of us have a time in our lives when we struggle to make sense of loss, and nothing can prepare you for that void’

From the time Ella was a puppy, I had a rule: whatever I did, she had to come too.
Invitations were always addressed to “James and Ella”. She has climbed all of the UK’s highest mountains with me, joined me on the red carpet, tried paddleboarding, camping under the stars . . . she even introduced me to my future wife.

Ella was my cocker spaniel, and earlier this month she died at the age of 15. When I first met her, she was four weeks old and I was 20. We grew up together, she looked out for me and I looked out for her.

Ella helped me to learn, especially during my days of depression, that talking and sharing can be a powerful, healing thing. That’s why I felt I needed to let people know and, with tears in my eyes, I shared the news about her on Instagram.
Thousands of people replied with their stories. Some sent letters or messages. There was even a drawing of Ella and me. The support and love that came my way has been incredible and overwhelming.

Whether you have had a dog or not, all of us have a time in our lives when we struggle to make sense of loss, and nothing can prepare you for that void. I suppose writing this has been my way of trying to process that loss, while hopefully helping others at the same time.

The Kansas City Chiefs were crowned Super Bowl champions for the third time in franchise history on Sunday in a nailbiting 38-35 victory over the Philadelphia Eagles.

This was such a bittersweet moment between brother duo @chiefs @killatrav and @philadelphiaeagles @jason.kelce. Travis told Jason, “I love you big brother,” before Jason urged Travis to “go celebrate.” 🥹❤️🏈

ICYMI ➡️ This was the first time that brothers played against each other on opposing teams in the 57 years since the Super Bowl began. 

Jason and Travis grew up in Ohio, although Jason, the older brother, was actually born in North Carolina. Jason is 35, and Travis is 33. They were both athletes at Cleveland Heights High School; Jason was both running back and linebacker with the football team, while Travis played basketball and soccer in addition to football. They then both went to the University of Cincinnati, Travis on a scholarship offer, and played for the Bearcats.

Jason was selected by the Eagles in the 2011 NFL Draft, and Travis was picked up by the Chiefs two years later.

“A sweet and sensible romance firmly placed in the real world . . . Meant to Be balances classic romance scenes with nuggets of history and nuanced takes on modern issues. . . . Giffin’s writing is consumable and rich, balancing dialogue and descriptions to build a parallel world with convincing characters. Meant to Be proves you can have your romance and think deeply, too.”—Associated Press
 
“This lively page-turner is inspired by the courtship of John F. Kennedy Jr. and Carolyn Bessette Kennedy.”—Elisabeth Egan, The New York Times 

“The novel strikes a careful balance between simply retelling the true story of JFK Jr. and his wife, Carolyn Bessette, and crafting an entirely new one. Readers who have an abiding interest in the Kennedys will be fascinated . . . Meant to Be is a chic, history-inspired summer read that you will want to take with you to the beach.”—Bookreporter

“Giffin reimagines the love story of John F. Kennedy, Jr., and Carolyn Bessette in her absorbing new novel. . . . Giffin convincingly dramatizes the challenges the couple faces, inducing readers to invest in them and hope desperately for a happy ending.” —Booklist

“If you’ve never read Emily Giffin, Meant to Be is the perfect place to start. This glorious, satisfying novel from the master storyteller of contemporary fiction is impossible to put down. It’s Giffin’s best novel yet—and they are all exceptional.”—Adriana Trigiani

“Meant to Be elegantly captures love in all its passionate, messy, wonderful glory. Emily Giffin’s writing is addictive—from the first page to the final line. This warm hug of a book is the perfect literary escape.”—Jill Santopolo
 
“I’m a sucker for an iconic, against-all-odds love story, and Meant to Be truly delivers. This fun, addictive read is a must for anyone enchanted by family dynasties, the private lives of the rich and famous, and soul connections that cannot be denied.”—Tia Williams 

“Meant To Be is the most golden, heart-crunching, epic love story, which swept me away into another time and another world.”—Sophie Kinsella

On April 5, 1987, seven-year-old Michelle Snow was killed by a lawn dart thrown by one of her brothers' playmates in the backyard of their home in Riverside, California, when the dart penetrated her skull and caused massive brain trauma. Snow’s father David began to advocate for a ban on lawn darts, claiming that there was no way to keep children from accessing lawn darts short of a full ban. As a result of Snow's lobbying, on December 19, 1988, the U.S. Consumer Product Safety Commission introduced an outright ban on lawn darts in the U.S. In the previous eight years, 6,100 Americans had visited hospital emergency rooms as the result of lawn-dart accidents. Of that total, 81% were 15 or younger, and half were 10 or younger.

A rainy but oh so wonderful Coronation Day. So happy to have witnessed this historic occasion. God Save The King! 🇬🇧

My favorite moment of The Coronation was when Prince William kneeled before his father, took his hands, and issued the Homage of Royal Blood, a similar pledge that Prince Philip issued to Queen Elizabeth II at her coronation in 1953. 

“I, William, Prince of Wales, pledge my loyalty to you and faith and truth I will bear unto you, as your liege man of life and limb. So help me God."

Afterwards, Prince William kissed his father’s cheek. King Charles replied with a simple and touching, “Thank you, William.” 

Swipe for more highlights of the service, including Prince George, second in line to the throne, holding his grandfather’s ceremonial robes and acting as one of The King’s four pages of honor.

Over the past 12 years, Edward, George, and Harriet have posed for thousands of photos in front of this house, their childhood home. It is where they learned the value of friendship and loyalty and hard work. They adopted two dogs, several fish, and a tortoise here. They raised chickens and ducks in the backyard. They built forts and swam in the pool and played sports and rode bikes and a gator. They hosted play dates and sleepovers and parties. They left for games and races and dances and dates. They attended school for a combined 34 years (!) and blew out dozens and dozens of birthday candles. They fought with each other and got in trouble and made up. They all fell in love for the first time while living here. They had their hearts broken from all kinds of disappointments but always came back stronger and more empathetic. They grew up here. We will forever cherish our memories of this time and place. Thank you for sharing so many moments with us along the way, including this final shot of the three of them together. ❤️

Travis Kelce was famous for several years—thanks to his Hall of Fame NFL résumé, his symbiotic relationship with Kansas City Chiefs teammate Patrick Mahomes—but that was just football famous. This year, after winning the Super Bowl, after hosting “Saturday Night Live,” after starring in all the commercials, Kelce became inescapable. And that was before—you know. ⁠
⁠
At the moment, the only thing millions of people want to know about Kelce’s future is whether or not it will include Taylor Swift. And the second thing they’re dying to know is how he and she got together in the first place. ⁠
⁠
More study has been dedicated to the opening salvos of their relationship than to the first seconds of the Big Bang, and thus far both origins remain a mystery. People have even speculated that Kelce somehow spoke his desire into the universe and just—manifested Swift? ⁠
⁠
Did he sit in a dark room and say “Jumanji” three times? He laughs. “I don’t know if I want to get into all of it,” he tells @wsjmag, and then he gets into it.⁠

GIFT ALERT! THE PALACE by @_garethrussell! I bought 3 copies of this gem. One for myself and 2 for the Anglophile/history lovers in my life. Can’t recommended enough. Swipe to see video of the author from the King’s coronation weekend 

🇬🇧🇬🇧🇬🇧

The popular and “scrupulous historian” (Daily Mail, London) Gareth Russell presents five hundred years of British history—from King Henry VIII to Queen Elizabeth II—as seen through the doorways of the exquisite Hampton Court Palace.

Architecturally breathtaking and rich in splendid art and décor, Hampton Court Palace has been the stage of some of the most important events in British history, such as the commissioning of King James’s version of the Bible, the staging of many of Shakespeare’s plays, and Queen Elizabeth II’s coronation ball.

Accessible, engaging, and unputdownable, The Palace takes us into every room in the castle, revealing the ups and downs of royal history and illustrating what was at play politically, socially, and economically at the time. An engaging and charming history book that is perfect for fans of Alison Weir, Philippa Gregory, and Andrew Lownie, The Palace makes you feel as if you were in the room as history was made.
